<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"  TextAlignment="Justify"   xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">

<Paragraph>Essential Presentation library has support for cloning individual slides in a PowerPoint presentation.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>This sample demonstrates cloning an individual slide from a PowerPoint presentation and merge it to another PowerPoint presentation with source and destination paste options.</Paragraph>
<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}"><Bold>Features:</Bold></TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Copy an individual PowerPoint slide and paste it to the same or different presentation.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Slide elements like text, shapes, charts, tables, SmartArt diagrams and images etc., can be copied and moved between PowerPoint presentations.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Copy the slides in a section and paste those to another section or PowerPoint presentation.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
<Paragraph>Note: This library supports creation, manipulation and conversion to PDF/image for .pptx format alone.</Paragraph>
